subSection.paragraph:
In ecological long-term experiments or in pristine habitats, destructive samplings like taking soil cores often are strongly limited to prevent destruction of the plots, and only small amounts of soil may be available for nematode extraction. Using large amounts of soil, on the other hand, may also reduce extraction efficiency as less mobile nematodes are discriminated (PM7/119(1) 2013, 
Ruess 1995
). Thus, exploring the role of the amount of extracted soil for nematode extraction efficiency is required to provide general recommendations.

